The paper deals with the complexity of expressing linear orders over a set of candidates using DNNF circuits. This topic falls under the scope of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as well as computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves the study of combinatorial objects such as linear orders, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and logic (cs.LO).
